{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cutoffDistance","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Float","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default value is 1.0 nm. This is 2.86σ for carbon and 2.45σ for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"silicon."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This documentation page is still a draft. It may be inconsistent or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"difficult to understand."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since germanium will rarely be used, use the 2.5σ cutoff for silicon. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"slightly greater sigma for carbon allows greater accuracy in vdW forces"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for bulk diamond. 1.0 nm is also sufficient for charge-charge","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interactions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the cutoff distance is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", nonbonded forces are computed with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"full O(n^2) cost. This may increase simulation speed for small-enough","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"systems and large-enough GPUs."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Required. The cutoff to use for nonbonded interactions.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefielddescriptor\/cutoffdistance"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"cutoffDistance"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Float","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"MM4"}],"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"cutoffDistance","externalID":"s:3MM40A20ForceFieldDescriptorV14cutoffDistanceSfSgvp","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor\/cutoffDistance"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor":{"type":"topic","title":"MM4ForceFieldDescriptor","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A configuration for a force field."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor","url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefielddescriptor","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4ForceFieldDescriptor"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4ForceFieldDescriptor"}]},"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor/cutoffDistance":{"title":"cutoffDistance","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldDescriptor\/cutoffDistance","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"cutoffDistance"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Float","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Required. The cutoff to use for nonbonded interactions."}],"url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefielddescriptor\/cutoffdistance"},"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Molecular Mechanics force field, version 4. The simulator used to create "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Nanosystems (1992)","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", but updated with modern ab initio parameters.","type":"text"}],"title":"MM4","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/mm4"}}}